reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality and Performance!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the Hisatey USB Extension Cable, and I must say, I am extremely satisfied with my purchase. This 20 ft long USB extender has exceeded my expectations in terms of quality, length, and product performance.First and foremost, the build quality of this cable is outstanding. The nylon braided design not only looks sleek but also feels incredibly durable. I can tell that this cable is made to last, with sturdy connectors that provide a secure and reliable connection between my devices.The length of the cable is perfect for my needs. I no longer have to worry about reaching awkwardly behind furniture or straining to connect my USB devices. The 20 ft length provides ample flexibility and convenience, allowing me to set up my devices exactly where I want them without any hassle.In terms of performance, this USB extension cable delivers flawless results. I have experienced no data loss or decrease in transfer speeds while using this cable. It efficiently transfers data and power between my devices, ensuring a seamless user experience. Whether I'm transferring large files or charging my devices, this cable gets the job done without any issues.Overall, I am highly impressed with the Hisatey USB Extension Cable. It combines excellent build quality, ample length, and top-notch performance, making it the ideal choice for anyone in need of a reliable USB extender. I would highly recommend this product to others, and I will definitely consider Hisatey for any future cable needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars if it lasts, it's a LIFESAVER
reviews.reviewText: I have only had this cable for two or three days, so be guided by other reviews on durability. That said, it's been a lifesaver. I got a new computer with three monitors. I put the desktop tower on my desk, and the monitors are BETWEEN the tower and the keyboard/mouse. My keyboard and mouse are a pair controlled by one usb chip-thingy that plugs into the tower's USB port. Even though my keyboard and mouse are about TWO FEET from tower, they were performing poorly, apparently due to the monitor blocking the signal. I had to put them up on the desk and close to the monitor, contorting my arms and neck for the whole workday. I decided to buy a cable like this, to allow the USB chip to dangle down the back of the tower to a point where it was below the monitor in the hope that that would solve the problem. I was worried that 1) it wouldn't work and 2) putting a cable between the USB chip and the tower would ALSO degrade the signal and cause the keyboard and monitor to be unresponsive. Well....I'm happy to report that my fix worked completely. There's no lag or anything. A complete fix. So if the cable lasts, I'll be completely satisfied.
